summary:
Rico Esquivel / Photographer, dancer, poet and film maker.
Mexican artist with wide international experience.

He studied Photography in Rome and has presented in different 
galleries. His work has also been published in magazines and for years he has worked in France, Holland, Italy, Switzerland, Spain, Belgium, Germany, United Kingdom, Japan, India, Morroco, and recently in Mexico.

His photography is a way to explore love, power, money, sexuality, spirituality and beauty of the body and soul among different countries.
 
He’s considered as an artist who generates “Beauty of Impact” by mixing
Art and Fashion

He’s currently working in Mexico in a Project about mithology and fashion,
and in the final process of a book and a shortfilm about personal identity.
